OL,3,CBirmingham City Hospital officially
OL,4,Ccloses as final patient leaves
OL,6,FThe site has had a hospital on it
OL,7,Fsince 1889, when it was built as an
OL,8,Fextension to the Birmingham Union
OL,9,FWorkhouse. It is well known for the
OL,10,Fmain corridor which is a third of a
OL,11,Fmile long, with nine Nightingale ward
OL,12,Fblocks radiating from it. It was the
OL,13,Fdesign from an architect called
OL,14,FW.H.Ward and designed around a
OL,15,Fconfiguration recommended by Florence
OL,16,FNightingale.
OL,18,FThe history of the building means
OL,19,Fthere are treasures to be spotted all
OL,20,Faround.
